Text.Value: But it's hard, because it means goodbye to our family's farm. Korson will never work those fields.
Three-Piece sounds like a crook. Better if you join the Fists.
Leave.
No, I guess I've had enough. The brewer who made this beer used to buy all of our barley. But that's over now.
That cleaner job sounds steady. Leaves you available to head back to the farm.
Oldest boy, Korson, he means well but he eats as much as the rest of us put together. I have to find him a place here.
The answer is yes - it's always yes.
Did  you try to fight back?
We used to sell our barley to the brewer who makes this very beer. That's all over now.
Life is meant for living! The boy must find his own path, as I did. As we all must.
Oldest boy, Korson, he means well but he eats as much as the rest of us put together. I have to find him a place here.
Korson's strong, but he's a gentle soul. Easy to take advantage of.
Of course, deep courage comes from a full belly.
Forget the city - the wilds have everything you need.
But you had enough left for a drink.
Left the crops standing in the fields when we ran from the Absolute army. Gone, all gone.
Huh - that's true. And we're no strangers to working the land.
If it were only me it wouldn't be so bad, but I've got mouths to feed.
Thanks, stranger, you helped settle my mind. Thanks are all I have to offer, though. May Ilmater bleed for you.
Will another drink solve your problems?
Another? Should I have another? Ilmater preserve me, I need the courage.
You look as out of place here as I feel.
Well good luck to you and your family.
One - and I shouldn't have had even that. Got work to do.
What will you country folk do here in the city?
Maybe I should just join the Flaming Fist and take the signing bonus. What else can I do?
I appreciate that some might find me a soft touch, but he's my son. I'll make no apology for looking out for him.
There's a war on. Can he fight?
What say you, should I have another? Ilmater preserve me, I need the courage.
You must be furious at the Absolute cult and their army.
A fancy feller called Three-Piece wants to place him as a cleaner in the Counting House. But I don't trust him.
I'm sure you'll find a new trade soon enough. There's plenty about.
Thanks again, stranger. Ilmater guide you.
I'm not so sure. What good can these farmer hands do in a city like this? Besides, I've got the others to think of.
Found any opportunities for him?
That's what I was thinking too. Was drinking to get up the courage to do it.
You won't find courage in the bottom of a bottle.
If he can't find his own place, perhaps he doesn't deserve one.
Huh. That's a solid tip. Could work out for a gentle kid like Korson.
Right. It's taking a chance, but it's worth the risk. The farm is all we have, really.
We? Who went with you?
Why? No more point to that than getting mad at a plague of locusts, or the weather.
A fancy feller called Three-Piece wants to place Korson as a cleaner in the Counting House. But I don't trust him.
The Thieves Guild are always on the lookout for talent. He'd never run out of work.
Drink up! This city is living on borrowed time.

Text.Value: We're farmers, not fighters. That's not the answer for us.
My gentle boy? A thief? I wouldn't have dared think of it before, but... maybe the Guild isn't a bad place to look.
No, saer. We abandoned our farm when the Absolute army marched in.
Family's upstairs, exhausted. I'm Dez Kanshaw - with a wife, two kids, and another on the way.
I'm sorry for your loss.
I hear the Ilmater temple at Wyrm's needs volunteers. They don't pay, but at least the boy will eat.
We? I see only you.
Thank you kindly. And to you and yours.
There's always room for anger. Especially in times like these.

Synopsis: Dez Kanshaw is a farmer with family woes.
